sentences: Sue Thompson (born Eva Sue McKee; July 19, 1925 – September 23, 2021) was an American pop and country music singer.
She was best known for the million selling hits "Sad Movies (Make Me Cry)" and "Norman", both pop hits in the early 1960s, and her 1965 hit "Paper Tiger".

Thompson was born in Nevada, Missouri in July 1925.
She married when she was 17, and had a daughter at 20, but the marriage failed and she and her husband split up after three years.

In 2009 Thompson recorded her favourite song “You Belong to Me” with her son, record producer Greg Penny.

Sue Thompson died at her daughter's home in Pahrump, Nevada, on September 23, 2021, at the age of 96.
